.TH _printf 3 "March 2026" "_printf manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- prints formatted output to standard output

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int_printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf prints characters, strings, integers, and percent signs to standard output.

.SS Conversion Specifiers
The following conversion speficiers are supported:
.TP
.B %c
Printf a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string. If the string is NULL, it prints "(null)".
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints an integer number using the helper function print_number.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.

If an unknown format specifier is provided, _printf prints the percent sign followed by the unknown character.

SH RETURN VALUE
The function returns the number of character printed.
If the input string is NULL or an incomplete format specifier is found,it returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
_printf("Hola %s\n", "Mundo"):
.br
Output:
Hola Mundo
.PP
_printf("Number: %d\n, 42);
.br
Output:
Number: 42
.PP
_printf("Character: %c\n", 'A');
.br
Output:
Character: A
.PP
_printf("Percent: %%\n");
.br
Output:
Percent: %

